The '''parrot-billed sparrow''' ('''''Passer gongonensis''''') is found in the arid lowlands of [[East Africa|eastern Africa]]. At {{convert|18|cm|in}} and {{convert|42|g|oz}}, it is the largest of the [[Old World sparrow|sparrow]]s of the [[Family (taxonomy)|family]] Passeridae. It is often considered a subspecies of the [[grey-headed sparrow]].

